Interface ILoadPluginCallback

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IRemoteBroker

    public interface ILoadPluginCallback
extends IRemoteBroker
    A callback class that monitors the plug-in download and installation status.

    The HUAWEI HiAI Engine server invokes this class.

    • Method Detail

      • onResult

        void onResult​(int resultCode)
       throws RemoteException
        Processes the plug-in installation result.

        The HUAWEI HiAI Engine server invokes this callback method to transfer the installation result code to onResult for further processing. The processing logic is defined by the client that has requested to download and install the plug-in. Different clients define different processing logic.

        Parameters:
        resultCode - Indicates the installation result code. Value 0 indicates a successful installation, and value 101 indicates an installation failure.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - Throws this exception if any error occurs when IRemoteObject is remotely invoked.
        Since:
        1

      • onProgress

        void onProgress​(int percentage)
         throws RemoteException
        Deals with the percentage of the downloaded plug-in size during the download and installation of a plug-in. The HUAWEI HiAI Engine server calculates the percentage of the downloaded plug-in size, and then invokes this callback method to deal with that percentage. The processing logic is defined by the client that has requested to download and install the plug-in.
        Parameters:
        percentage - Indicates the percentage of the downloaded plug-in size. The value ranges from 0 to 1.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - Throws this exception if any error occurs when IRemoteObject is remotely invoked.
        Since:
        1
